{
  "texts": [
    "The epimorphism, monomorphism and automorphism matrices are integral and 𝐻 = 𝐸𝐴𝑀.By [Yos87, §4.2], the epimorphism matrix is conjugate to a lower triangular matrix, the monomorphism matrix is conjugate to an upper triangular one and the automorphism matrix is diagonal, hence the decomposition of 𝐻 from Theorem 2.3 implies that det(𝐻) = 𝑐∈C |Aut(𝑐)|, which is non-zero since Aut(𝑐) ≠ ∅ for every 𝑐 ∈ C. It follows that the hom-set matrix is rationally invertible and the Burnside homomorphism is an isomorphism.Lemma 2.4.",
    "Let C be a finite skeletal category.",
    "If C has an epi-mono factorization system, then the rational Burnside homomorphism𝜙: 𝐴 Q (C) -→ Q C, is an isomorphism.",
    "In particular, 𝐴 Q (C) is a rational abstract Burnside ring.Remark 2.5.",
    "The rational situation is quite different from the integral case."
  ]
}